HEADWORD: Prebronchial
<hw>Pre*bron"chi*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated in front of the bronchus; -- applied especially to an air
sac on either side of the esophagus of birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

